      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If a child asked their mum for a Zelda game and she said that they had Zelda at home, she'd be referring to ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Rogue Heroes",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". It has all the makings of a quality topdown action-adventure game and it's made all the more enjoyable when played with friends, but it leaves a little to be desired in the personality department. It's a fun game that has a lot to offer, but it just doesn't go anywhere beyond that.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
